<element xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xmlns:zenta="http://magwas.rulez.org/zenta"
         xsi:type="zenta:BasicObject"
         name="Utility Class"
         id="3c4d5358-9776-4954-a912-5d8c45183628"
         ancestor="thing">
   <documentation>A utility class holds code implementing behaviour, which is either

* overflown from Service or Controller units due to code complexity constraints, or
* used by more Controllers, Services ot Utility classes, and
* can be tested through the interface of Controller and Service units, therefore no need to crete their own Service.

If the utility class is for input validation logic, it should be placed in the same package as the validated DTO.

</documentation>
